value.title: Notable names on Trump's list of potential Supreme Court nominees
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump has updated a roster of more than 20 potential Supreme Court nominees in recent weeks, a list that includes prominent and lesser-known conservatives who would undoubtedly tilt the court further rightward if one were appointed.

value.title: Joe Biden mourns Ruth Bader Ginsburg and says she shouldn't be replaced until after the election
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee and former Vice President Joe Biden mourned the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg on Friday and demanded that voters dictate the next president before her replacement is chosen.

value.title: Rep. Engel agrees to drop Pompeo subpoena now that he has Biden documents
value.excerpt: House Foreign Affairs Chairman Eliot Engel on Friday agreed to withdraw a subpoena he had issued in July against Secretary of State Mike Pompeo after the State Department turned over more than 16,000 pages of documents the committee had sought, the panel announced.

value.title: Trump at Minnesota rally: Biden will turn state into a 'refugee camp'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump said his Democratic rival Joe Biden would "turn Minnesota into a refugee camp" and bragged about deporting Somali nationals, sharpening his play for the battleground state during a Friday rally.

value.title: Trump reacts to Ruth Bader Ginsburg’s death, says justice ‘led an amazing life’
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday called late Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg “an amazing woman who led an amazing life” and said he was “sad” to learn of her passing, but didn't say anything about plans for nominating a replacement.

value.title: Trump calls mail-in voting a scam, says Democrats are setting up election 'mess'
value.excerpt: President Trump called mail-in voting a “scam” during a Friday press conference, attempting to draw a line between people that specifically request absentee ballots, and states where mail-in ballots are being widely issued.
